.TH "freeze_task" 9 "freeze_task" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
freeze_task \- send a freeze request to given task
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" freeze_task
.BI "(struct task_struct *p "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "p" 12
task to send the request to
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If \fIp\fP is freezing, the freeze request is sent either by sending a fake
signal (if it's not a kernel thread) or waking it up (if it's a kernel
thread).
.SH "RETURN"
false, if \fIp\fP is not freezing or already frozen; true, otherwise
